e": "Freddie Green", "qid": "Q722441", "roles": ["guitar"]}, {"id": "24822", "name": "Harry Edison", "qid": "Q289821", "roles": ["trumpet"]}, {"id": "26106", "name": "James P. Johnson", "qid": "Q550541", "roles": ["piano"]}, {"id": "28712", "name": "Jimmy Rushing", "qid": "Q1689431", "roles": ["vocalist"]}, {"id": "29439", "name": "Dan Minor", "qid": "Q5214034", "roles": ["trombone"]}, {"id": "31322", "name": "Count Basie", "qid": "Q107008", "roles": ["piano"]}, {"id": "32134", "name": "Julius Davis", "qid": null, "roles": ["tenor"]}, {"id": "41293", "name": "Herschel Evans", "qid": "Q491395", "roles": ["tenor_saxophone"]}, {"id": "42563", "name": "Tommy Ladnier", "qid": "Q489563", "roles": ["trumpet"]}, {"id": "43342", "name": "Pete Johnson", "qid": "Q1399599", "roles": ["piano"]}, {"id": "47182", "name": "Dicky Wells", "qid": "Q350879", "roles": ["trombone"]}, {"id": "49906", "name": "Big Bill Broonzy", "qid": "Q449239", "roles": ["vocalist"]}, {"id": "49909", "name": "Meade Lux Lewis", "qid": "Q1399605", "roles": ["piano"]}, {"id": "51368", "name": "Louis David", "qid": null, "roles": ["baritone"]}, {"id": "53447", "name": "Helen Humes", "qid": "Q129252", "roles": ["vocalist"]}, {"id": "54061", "name": "Shad Collins", "qid": "Q1351942", "roles": ["trumpet"]}, {"id": "56248", "name": "William Brown", "qid": null, "roles": ["tenor"]}, {"id": "58121", "name": "Buck Clayton", "qid": "Q999321", "roles": ["trumpet"]}, {"id": "64065", "name": "John Hammond", "qid": null, "roles": ["host"]}, {"id": "64403", "name": "Big Joe Turner", "qid": "Q358350", "roles": ["vocalist"]}]}], "quotes": [{"speaker": "Helen Humes", "qid": "Q129252", "text": "And I said, \"oh my goodness I haven't even hummed since I've been home. I can't do nothing\". He said, \"yes you can Helen. Now you can sing.\" I said, \"well it's been so long I don't know whether I can sing or not\". He said, \"well why don't you come on and try\". I said, \"because Carnegie Hall is too big to be trying to sing in\". And so he said, \"well, just come on, you can make it\". And I said, \"well, alright then, if you think I can make I'll come on and sing something\". So I went on and Nellie Lutcher, bless her heart, she came and she said, \"Helen I'll stay right here with you until you go on\". She said, \"don't be scared\". And I said, \"well you know every time I get nervous and I get hoarse and everything\". She ran across the street to the drug store and she brought me more cough drops and cough syrups and stuff. And I said, \"well if I ain't feeling better now, I won't\". And I went on and it was sensational.", "caption": "Helen Humes' nervous debut at From Spirituals to Swing", "conf": "medium", "first_person": true, "doc_title": "67255_Helen Humes oral history interview", "collection": "rutgers", "url": "https://rucore.libraries.rutgers.edu/rutgers-lib/67255/"}, {"speaker": "Joe Turner", "qid": "Q358350", "text": "During World War Number Two. And, uh, we were runnin' back and forth to New York an' all over the country. Gettin' back to New York, I was uh...forgot to tell you that the first blues show that ever was at Carnegie Hall, John Hammond gave it, an' I was on the show. Had Big Bill from Chicago, a host of other blues singers... Big Bill had on some tight shoes were hurtin' his feet. He would stand up on the stage playin' and cryin'.", "caption": "Joe Turner recalls the first blues show at Carnegie Hall", "conf": "high", "first_person": true, "doc_title": "68091_Joe Turner oral history interview", "collection": "rutgers", "url": "https://rucore.libraries.rutgers.edu/rutgers-lib/68091/"}], "featured_people": [{"qid": "Q731178", "id": "4712", "name": "Albert Ammons"}, {"qid": "Q352013", "id": "9795", "name": "Benny Morton"}, {"qid": "Q449239", "id": "49906", "name": "Big Bill Broonzy"}, {"qid": "Q358350", "id": "64403", "name": "Big Joe Turner"}, {"qid": "Q999321", "id": "58121", "name": "Buck Clayton"}, {"qid": "Q107008", "id": "31322", "name": "Count Basie"}, {"qid":